&lt;td&gt;80&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Defeat illusion with auditory component&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
      &lt;div topic=&quot;Defeat Illusion&quot; level=&quot;8&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Defeat Illusion:&lt;/b&gt; The character can automatically detect any illusion with an auditory component for what it truly is. No Will save is required, and the character doesn't have to interact with the illusion (but he or she must be able to hear its auditory component). Special: A character can use Listen to notice the presence of an invisible creature (generally opposed by a Move Silently check). If the character beats the DC by 20 or more, he or she can pinpoint the location of the invisible creature, though it still maintains total concealment from the character (50% miss chance).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p/&gt;&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

