skill_check:
&lt;p&gt; You generally must be within 10 feet of the object or surface to be searched. The table below gives DCs for typical tasks involving the Search skill.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p/&gt;&lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; cellspacing=&quot;2&quot; frame=&quot;VOID&quot; rules=&quot;ROWS&quot;&gt;

&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;b&gt;Task&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;td&gt;&lt;b&gt;Search DC&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Ransack a chest full of junk to find a certain item&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;10&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Notice a typical secret door or a simple trap&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;20&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Find a difficult nonmagical trap (rogue only)&lt;b&gt;1&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;21 or higher&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Find a magic trap (rogue only)&lt;b&gt;1&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;25 + level of spell used to create trap&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Notice a well-hidden secret door&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;30&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Find a footprint&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Varies&lt;sup&gt;&lt;b&gt;2&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;1 Dwarves (even if they are not rogues) can use Search to find traps built into or out of stone.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr maxcol=&quot;3&quot; curcol=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
&lt;td colspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;2 A successful Search check can find a footprint or similar sign of a creature's passage, but it won't let you find or follow a trail. See the Track feat for the appropriate DC.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p/&gt;

